Contributors looking for a mission:

  * Just do an egrep on "TODO", "XXX" or "FIXME" in the source.
  * Review the bug database at: http://bugzilla.ganglia.info/
  * Open bugs in the bug database.
  * Implement a feature from the wishlist at: http://sourceforge.net/apps/trac/ganglia/wiki/ganglia_wish-list

CURRENT RELEASE NOTES:
  (Please update this area with a brief description of bug fixes and
   enhancements that have been backported for the current release)

  3.1.8:

  * build: `make install` target now installs manpages automatically

RELEASE SHOWSTOPPERS:

  * None outstanding

BACKPORT PROPOSALS:

  * Security:  Set more restrictive umask for RRD file creation.
    Description at http://bugzilla.ganglia.info/cgi-bin/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=229
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia?view=rev&revision=1986
    +1: hawson
    -1: carenas
    carenas: proposal changes gmetad's default behaviour and assumptions
             alternative backport suggested in ATT191

  * web: performance/security improvement for handling authorization
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia?view=rev&revision=1588
    +1: carenas
    +0: hawson
    -1: bernardli
    bernardli: PHP would look in the current directory for the file to include,
               therefore, adding the "./" is redundant.  In fact I would propose
               that we get rid of all the "./" for the other include_once()
               calls in web/*.
    hawson: If security is an issue, then check/set the include path with
            the get_include_path() and set_include_path() functions.  I don't
            see that this would affect performance much.

  * build: libmetrics dependency cleanup
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia?view=rev&revision=1597
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia?view=rev&revision=1602
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia?view=rev&revision=1603
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia?view=rev&revision=1612
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia?view=rev&revision=1614
    +1: carenas
    carenas: prerequisite for mingw32 support, RPC/ON is used in core only

  * build: remove sideffects of --disable-python for dist target
    http://www.mail-archive.com/ganglia-developers@lists.sourceforge.net/msg04551.html
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia?view=rev&revision=1610
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia?view=rev&revision=1877
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia?view=rev&revision=1880
    +1: carenas
    -1: bnicholes
    bnicholes: There seems to be several problems with this patch. First the
      configure fails because the example directory was not included in the
      DIST_SUBDIRS and therefore none of the example source or make files are
      included in the final tarball. Second, since the .pyc are not being
      generated, the spec file fails when it tries to copy the missing .pyc
      files.
    bnicholes: Patch r1877 fixed the first issue with the inclusion of the
      example source, but the second issue still remains.
    carenas: updated proposal, re-vote required

  * python_modules: remove unconditional debugging information for multidisk
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia?view=rev&revision=1623
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia?view=rev&revision=2146
    +1: carenas

  * libmetrics: mingw32 (native windows) support
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia?view=rev&revision=1599
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia?view=rev&revision=1600
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia?view=rev&revision=1601
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia?view=rev&revision=1603
    +1: carenas, bnicholes
    carenas: depends on libmetrics dependency cleanup

  * Web-Interface: Add "Avg Load percentages and overall cluster utilization"
    http://bugzilla.ganglia.info/cgi-bin/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=193
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia?view=rev&revision=1594
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia?view=rev&revision=1706
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia?view=rev&revision=1708
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia?view=rev&revision=1754
    +1: hawson
    -1: twitham
    twitham: Prefer the following option instead.  Recalculating this
             number takes more time and it is not obvious where it
             originates from (CPU?  Load?).  Just let RRD do it and
             display it in the graph legends so user has more
             information.  And do away with this redundant number.

  * Web-Interface: Add statistics and numbers to various charts and reports.
    http://bugzilla.ganglia.info/cgi-bin/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=206
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia?view=rev&revision=1753
    http://bugzilla.ganglia.info/cgi-bin/bugzilla/attachment.cgi?id=173&action=view
    +0.5: carenas
    +1: hawson -- really should go with r1753 as well.
    +1: twitham
    twitham: the proposal missed corresponding tweaks to metric.php
        and sample_report.php.  The full backport should be revisions
        1844, 1847, 1848, 1850, 1855, 1856, 1857, like this:
        http://bugzilla.ganglia.info/cgi-bin/bugzilla/attachment.cgi?id=175&action=view
    carenas: original proposal incomplete, should be replaced with twitham's

  * gmetric: Add support for group, description and title metadata tags for
    metrics collected via gmetric
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia?view=rev&revision=1875
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia?view=rev&revision=1876
    +1: bernardli, carenas, bnicholes
    carenas: patched generated files; cleanup to follow

  * Web-Interface:  Change line widths on 'small' graph sizes for the stock
    {load,network,packet}_report.php files.
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia?view=rev&revision=2083
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia?view=rev&revision=2085
    +1: hawson, bernardli

  * gmetad:  Don't store every spoof host name that is spoofing the same
     metric in the metric summary data for the metric.  This was causing 
     the string array buffer in the hash table to overflow and prevent the 
     summary data from being stored in rrd.
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia?view=rev&revision=2277
    +1: bnicholes

  * web: Replace deprecated function split() with explode()
    https://sourceforge.net/apps/trac/ganglia/changeset/2326
    +1: bernardli

